Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay near fine light buff-brown. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 121, 18. Name Philodamos. Athenian Agora SS2199, unpublished, is from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0880)
